<white>synopsys:</>
    the command <green>show</> is used to display informations about 
    usernames, groups, and configured websites.

<white>usage: </>
    <green>show</> <yellow>users</>
    or
    <green>show</> <yellow>groups</>
    or
    <green>show</> <yellow>websites</>
    
<white>arguments:</>
    <yellow>users</>  - display the list of available users <red>in the 
            current website context</>.
            
            <red>!</> <cyan>by using this argument, it is assumed that you 
            allready </><green>use</><cyan>d a website before.</>
            
    <yellow>groups</> - display the list of available groups <red>in the 
            current website context</>.
            
            <red>!</> <cyan>by using this argument, it is assumed that you 
            allready </><green>use</><cyan>d a website before.</>
            
    <yellow>websites</> - displays the list of configured onedb 
            websites.
            
            this argument does not require a website context to run.

<white>examples:</>
    <green>show</> <yellow>users</>
    <green>show</> <yellow>groups</>
    <green>show</> <yellow>websites</>

<white>notes:</>
    this command supports only one argument. <red>you cannot</> issue a 
    <green>show</> <yellow>users</> <yellow>websites</>.